The paper discusses a new recurrent neural network architecture designed for interpretability, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on a specific type of neural network and its performance on a text modeling task. The paper also discusses the use of linear methods to analyze the network, which is relevant to the sub-field of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of neural networks for interpretability is a topic of interest in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper's focus on the architecture's computational efficiency may also make it relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the text modeling task may make the paper relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision), as natural language processing is often a sub-field of computer vision.
